## Common Edits (Recipes)

### Add a new AI provider or model
1. Define model identifiers and defaults in [AppConstants.swift](mdc:Warden/Configuration/AppConstants.swift).
2. Implement a handler conforming to [APIProtocol.swift](mdc:Warden/Utilities/APIHandlers/APIProtocol.swift).
3. Register it in [APIServiceFactory.swift](mdc:Warden/Utilities/APIHandlers/APIServiceFactory.swift).
4. Ensure request formatting via [RequestMessagesTransformer.swift](mdc:Warden/Models/RequestMessagesTransformer.swift) and [MessageManager.swift](mdc:Warden/Utilities/MessageManager.swift).
5. Parse/stream responses in the handler and via [MessageParser.swift](mdc:Warden/Utilities/MessageParser.swift) (include reasoning streams when applicable).
6. Update model visibility and preferences using [SelectedModelsManager.swift](mdc:Warden/Utilities/SelectedModelsManager.swift) and [FavoriteModelsManager.swift](mdc:Warden/Utilities/FavoriteModelsManager.swift).

### Handle reasoning-capable models
- Convert system messages to user role before sending.
- Surface reasoning content separately and render via [ThinkingProcessView.swift](mdc:Warden/UI/Chat/ThinkingProcessView.swift).
- Temperature and similar parameters may be ignored by some reasoning models; prefer service defaults.

### Add or modify chat UI features
- Edit view/state in [ChatView.swift](mdc:Warden/UI/Chat/ChatView.swift) and [ChatViewModel.swift](mdc:Warden/UI/Chat/ChatViewModel.swift).
- For multi-agent, coordinate via [MultiAgentMessageManager.swift](mdc:Warden/Utilities/MultiAgentMessageManager.swift) and render in [MultiAgentResponseView.swift](mdc:Warden/UI/Chat/MultiAgentResponseView.swift).

### Work with attachments
- Use [ImageAttachment.swift](mdc:Warden/Models/ImageAttachment.swift) and [FileAttachment.swift](mdc:Warden/Models/FileAttachment.swift) to extract, type-detect, and send content.
- Provide previews/components under [UI/Components](mdc:Warden/UI/Components/).

### Persistence & indexing
- Use [ChatStore.swift](mdc:Warden/Store/ChatStore.swift) for Core Data operations.
- Keep Spotlight index consistent via [SpotlightIndexManager.swift](mdc:Warden/Utilities/SpotlightIndexManager.swift).

## Guardrails & Best Practices
- **Privacy**: Never log API keys or sensitive message content.
- **Streaming**: Always clean up streaming connections; support cancellation.
- **Reasoning**: Check for reasoning capability and handle dual streams (reasoning + content).
- **Performance**: Prefer async/await and structured concurrency; avoid blocking the main thread.
- **UI consistency**: Follow existing SwiftUI patterns and component styles under [Warden/UI](mdc:Warden/UI).
- **Accessibility**: Ensure VoiceOver labels, keyboard navigation; see [accessibility-localization.mdc](mdc:.cursor/rules/accessibility-localization.mdc).
- **Testing**: Add/adjust tests in [WardenTests](mdc:WardenTests) and [WardenUITests](mdc:WardenUITests) for new functionality.

